label.value: detection of pH by chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which information about the levels of hydrogen ions are received and are converted to a molecular signal by chemoreceptors.

label.value: baroreceptor detection of increased arterial stretch

value.value: The series of events by which an increase in diameter of an artery is detected and converted to a molecular signal.

label.value: baroreceptor detection of decreased arterial stretch

value.value: The series of events by which a decrease in diameter of an artery is detected and converted to a molecular signal.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by baroreceptor feedback

value.value: The neural regulation of blood pressure in which baroreceptors sense the amount of stretch occurring in vessels and respond to the input via central nervous system control.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by aortic arch baroreceptor feedback

value.value: The process that modulates blood pressure by sensing the amount of stretch occurring in the aorta and responding to the input via central nervous system control.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by carotid body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process that modulates blood pressure by the action of chemoreceptors found in the carotid bodies and their resultant modulation of the vasomotor center. Chemoreceptors respond to oxygen, carbon dioxide and hydrogen ions.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by aortic body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process that modulates blood pressure by the action of chemoreceptors found in the aortic bodies and their resultant modulation of the vasomotor center. Chemoreceptors respond to oxygen, carbon dioxide and hydrogen ions.

label.value: detection of hypoxic conditions in blood by carotid body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which information about a lack of oxygen are received and are converted to a molecular signal by chemoreceptors in the carotid bodies.

label.value: detection of hydrogen ion

value.value: The series of events in which a hydrogen ion stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal.

label.value: detection of carbon dioxide

value.value: The series of events in which a carbon dioxide stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal.

label.value: detection of oxygen

value.value: The series of events in which an oxygen stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal.

label.value: detection of hypoxic conditions in blood by aortic body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which information about a lack of oxygen are received and are converted to a molecular signal by chemoreceptors in the aortic bodies.

label.value: detection of increased carbon dioxide by aortic body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which information about the levels of carbon dioxide are received and are converted to a molecular signal by chemoreceptors in an aortic body.

label.value: detection of increased carbon dioxide by carotid body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which information about the levels of carbon dioxide are received and are converted to a molecular signal by chemoreceptors in a carotid body.

label.value: detection of pH by aortic body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which information about the levels of hydrogen ions are received and are converted to a molecular signal by chemoreceptors in an aortic body.

label.value: detection of pH by carotid body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which information about the levels of hydrogen ions are received and are converted to a molecular signal by chemoreceptors in a carotid body.

label.value: detection of reduced oxygen by aortic body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which information about the levels of oxygen are received and are converted to a molecular signal by chemoreceptors in an aortic body.

label.value: detection of reduced oxygen by carotid body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which information about the levels of oxygen are received and are converted to a molecular signal by chemoreceptors in a carotid body.

label.value: excitation of vasomotor center by aortic body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which the molecular signal from an aortic body is relayed to the vasomotor center, causing it to signal an increase arterial pressure.

label.value: excitation of vasomotor center by carotid body chemoreceptor signaling

value.value: The process in which the molecular signal from a carotid body is relayed to the vasomotor center, causing it to signal an increase arterial pressure.

label.value: vasoconstriction of artery involved in carotid body chemoreceptor response to lowering of systemic arterial blood pressure

value.value: A process that is triggered by carotid body-vasomotor excitation and results in a decrease in the diameter of an artery during the chemoreceptor response to decreased blood pressure.

label.value: vasoconstriction of artery involved in aortic body chemoreceptor response to lowering of systemic arterial blood pressure

value.value: A process that is triggered by aortic body-vasomotor excitation and results in a decrease in the diameter of an artery during the chemoreceptor response to decreased blood pressure.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure mediated by a chemical signal

value.value: The regulation of blood pressure mediated by biochemical signaling: hormonal, autocrine or paracrine.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by physical factors

value.value: The regulation of blood pressure mediated by detection of forces within the circulatory system.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by stress relaxation

value.value: The intrinsic circulatory process resulting from stress relaxation that modulates the force with which blood travels through the systemic arterial circulatory system. Stress relaxation is the adaptation of vessels to a new size as a result of changes in pressure in storage areas such as veins, the liver, the spleen, and the lungs.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by epinephrine

value.value: The regulation of blood pressure mediated by the catecholamine signaling molecule epinephrine.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by norepinephrine

value.value: The regulation of blood pressure mediated by the catecholamine signaling molecule norepinephrine.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by capillary fluid shift

value.value: The intrinsic circulatory process resulting from capillary fluid shift that modulates the force with which blood travels through the systemic arterial circulatory system. Capillary fluid shift is the movement of fluid across the capillary membrane between the blood and the interstitial fluid compartment.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by atrial natriuretic peptide

value.value: The regulation of blood pressure mediated by the signaling molecule atrial natriuretic peptide.

label.value: angiotensin-mediated drinking behavior

value.value: The drinking behavior that is mediated by the action of angiotensin in the brain. Angiotensin stimulates the brain centers that control thirst.

label.value: circadian regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure

value.value: Any process in which an organism modulates its blood pressure at different values with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

label.value: circadian regulation of heart rate

value.value: Any process in which an organism modulates its heart rate at different values with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

label.value: circadian regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by the suprachiasmatic nucleus

value.value: The process in which the suprachiasmatic nucleus modulates blood pressure at different values with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

label.value: circadian regulation of heart rate by the suprachiasmatic nucleus

value.value: The process in which the suprachiasmatic nucleus modulates heart rate at different values with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

label.value: regulation of vascular associated smooth muscle contraction

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of vascular smooth muscle contraction.

label.value: regulation of the force of heart contraction by chemical signal

value.value: The regulation of the force of heart muscle contraction mediated by chemical signaling, hormonal, autocrine or paracrine.

label.value: hormonal regulation of the force of heart contraction

value.value: The process in which the hormones modulates the force of heart muscle contraction. A hormone is one of a group of substances formed in very small amounts in one specialized organ or group of cells and carried (sometimes in the bloodstream) to another organ or group of cells, in the same organism, upon which they have a specific regulatory action.

label.value: positive regulation of the force of heart contraction by epinephrine

value.value: The process in which the secretion of epinephrine into the bloodstream or released from nerve endings modulates the force of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: negative regulation of the force of heart contraction by acetylcholine

value.value: The process in which acetylcholine released from vagus nerve endings binds to muscarinic receptors and decreases the force of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of the force of heart contraction by norepinephrine

value.value: The process in which the secretion of norepinephrine into the bloodstream or released from nerve endings modulates the force of heart musclecontraction.

label.value: regulation of heart rate by chemical signal

value.value: The regulation of the rate of heart contraction mediated by chemical signaling, hormonal, autocrine or paracrine.

label.value: negative regulation of heart rate by acetylcholine

value.value: The process in which acetylcholine released from vagus nerve endings binds to muscarinic receptors on the pacemaker cells and decreases the rate of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: regulation of heart rate by hormone

value.value: The process in which the hormones modulates the rate of heart muscle contraction. A hormone is one of a group of substances formed in very small amounts in one specialized organ or group of cells and carried (sometimes in the bloodstream) to another organ or group of cells, in the same organism, upon which they have a specific regulatory action.

label.value: positive regulation of heart rate by epinephrine

value.value: The process in which the secretion of epinephrine into the bloodstream or released from nerve endings increases the rate of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: positive regulation of heart rate by norepinephrine

value.value: The process in which the secretion of norepinephrine into the bloodstream or released from nerve endings increases the rate of heart muscle contraction.

label.value: circadian regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by hormone

value.value: The process in which hormones modulate the force with which blood passes through the circulatory system contributing to different values of blood pressure oscillating with a regularity of approximately 24 hours. A hormone is one of a group of substances formed in very small amounts in one specialized organ or group of cells and carried (sometimes in the bloodstream) to another organ or group of cells, in the same organism, upon which they have a specific regulatory action.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by acetylcholine

value.value: The regulation of blood pressure mediated by acetylcholine signaling. Acetylcholine is an acetic acid ester of the organic base choline and functions as a neurotransmitter.

label.value: acetylcholine-mediated vasodilation involved in regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure

value.value: The process in which acetylcholine signaling causes vasodilation, resulting in a change in blood pressure.

label.value: regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure by neurotransmitter

value.value: The regulation of blood pressure mediated by a neurotransmitter. A neurotransmitter is any of a group of substances that are released on excitation from the axon terminal of a presynaptic neuron of the central or peripheral nervous system and travel across the synaptic cleft to either excite or inhibit the target cell.

label.value: renal system process involved in regulation of systemic arterial blood pressure

value.value: Renal process that modulates the force with which blood travels through the circulatory system. The process is controlled by a balance of processes that increase pressure and decrease pressure.
